messages.message:
hi all - i received the following question from one of my prospective customers - The demo was good and helpful for understanding capability of your product. Architecturally, one of our next steps to dig into the feasibility of deployment in TD azure tenant, e.g. an azure service can be provisioned and consumed by TD within the TD azure space, and can be integrated with other azure services. If you can share any documentation or website links, would be very helpful

Do we have any documentation around this? Or things we can highlight?

Instabase is deployed on Kubernetes, so they can deploy  us onto AKS. Is this what they’re asking? 
“Can we deploy Instabase in Azure?”
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-gb/services/kubernetes-service/ (https://azure.microsoft.com/en-gb/services/kubernetes-service/)
What is the TD acronym above?
@Matt Weaver TD is the name of the company :joy:
